3 SECTION 32. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3100.32 of Title 63, unless
5 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 Upon motion by any party to enjoin the implementation of a
7 health care decision by a surrogate to provide, withhold, or
8 withdraw life sustaining care, the court shall issue an order
9 requiring that, pending a final decision on the merits and the
10 resolution of any appeal, the individual be provided with health
11 care which, in reasonable medical judgment, is necessary to prevent
12 the individual’s death. The court shall not order the provision of
13 such care if doing so would require the denial of the same health
14 care to another individual.
